text: Angela Walch is talking about her paper Open Source Risks for Financial Markets, ties directly to Jeremy Sevareid's Requirements Strawman on <https://cyber.stanford.edu/blockchainconf>  (see link for paper)

attachments.title: Blockchain Protocol Analysis and Security Engineering 2017 | Cyber Initiative
attachments.text: January 26-27 2017, Paul Brest Hall, Stanford University We have reached registration capacity; thank you for your interest! The conference will explore the use of formal methods, empirical analysis, and risk modeling to better understand security and systemic risk in blockchain protocols.  The conference aims to foster multidisciplinary collaboration among practitioners and researchers in blockchain protocols, distributed systems, cryptography, computer security, and risk management.
